1
00:00:14,521 --> 00:00:18,670
The kettle wakes the kitchen with a hiss,

2
00:00:18,670 --> 00:00:20,265
Then there is this,

3
00:00:20,265 --> 00:00:21,861
upon my cheek -

4
00:00:21,861 --> 00:00:24,335
a soft little kiss.

5
00:00:24,335 --> 00:00:26,888
The ordinary weight -

6
00:00:26,888 --> 00:00:28,403
of a cup of tea.

7
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:30,878
This stuff right here,

8
00:00:30,878 --> 00:00:33,959
just you and me.

9
00:00:34,308 --> 00:00:39,176
Rain on the rooftop of the world,

10
00:00:39,176 --> 00:00:43,164
Tiny tangled oaken brown curled.

11
00:00:43,164 --> 00:00:46,197
I've come back into something,

12
00:00:46,197 --> 00:00:47,472
the scene of this.

13
00:00:47,472 --> 00:00:54,095
Right in the moments that I miss.

14
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:58,963
Am I to know this right, was wrong?

15
00:00:58,963 --> 00:01:04,069
Am I the one who really wrote this song?

16
00:01:04,069 --> 00:01:07,739
Secrets written between the lines,

17
00:01:07,739 --> 00:01:12,846
Find them one by one,

18
00:01:12,846 --> 00:01:21,911
yours and mine.

19
00:01:22,260 --> 00:01:27,367
Tiny feed across the matted floor,

20
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:31,834
A little figure standing by the door.

21
00:01:31,834 --> 00:01:34,308
Sweet daffodil of mine,

22
00:01:34,308 --> 00:01:41,060
Was this all by design?

23
00:01:41,409 --> 00:01:44,043
Something in the chest still hums a note,

24
00:01:44,043 --> 00:01:50,584
An old and half-remembered antidote —

25
00:01:50,584 --> 00:01:53,617
It calls me to the high, the thin, the free,

26
00:01:53,617 --> 00:02:01,724
Our hearth was lit by you, by me.

27
00:02:02,073 --> 00:02:07,340
Rain on the rooftop of the world,

28
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:12,206
Little strands round my fingers curled.

29
00:02:12,206 --> 00:02:16,037
The very scent, can I now recall,

30
00:02:16,037 --> 00:02:17,473
Swear, I'd give anything,

31
00:02:17,473 --> 00:02:22,181
anything at all.

32
00:02:22,181 --> 00:02:27,366
Am I to know that I belong?

33
00:02:27,366 --> 00:02:32,074
How do we judge this right or wrong?

34
00:02:32,074 --> 00:02:36,144
Secrets are written between the lines,

35
00:02:36,144 --> 00:02:41,856
Find them one by one, yours and mine.

36
00:02:42,206 --> 00:02:50,105
The kettle goes quiet,

37
00:02:50,105 --> 00:02:52,659
A little riot, a roar,

38
00:02:52,659 --> 00:02:57,686
Miss those days that came before,

39
00:02:57,686 --> 00:03:00,479
But most of all,

40
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:03,111
of that I miss.

41
00:03:03,111 --> 00:03:08,138
upon my cheek

42
00:03:08,138 --> 00:03:11,967
that little kiss,
